26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_mc_nv04.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:34 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "priv.h"
30
31const struct nvkm_mc_intr
32nv04_mc_intr[] = {
33 { 0x00000001, NVKM_ENGINE_MPEG }, /* NV17- MPEG/ME */
34 { 0x00000100, NVKM_ENGINE_FIFO },
35 { 0x00001000, NVKM_ENGINE_GR },
36 { 0x00010000, NVKM_ENGINE_DISP },
37 { 0x00020000, NVKM_ENGINE_VP }, /* NV40- */
38 { 0x00100000, NVKM_SUBDEV_TIMER },
39 { 0x01000000, NVKM_ENGINE_DISP }, /* NV04- PCRTC0 */
40 { 0x02000000, NVKM_ENGINE_DISP }, /* NV11- PCRTC1 */
41 { 0x10000000, NVKM_SUBDEV_BUS },
42 { 0x80000000, NVKM_ENGINE_SW },
43 {}
44};
45
46void
47nv04_mc_intr_unarm(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
48{
49 struct nvkm_device *device = mc->subdev.device;
50 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x000140, 0x00000000);
51 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x000140);
52}
53
54void
55nv04_mc_intr_rearm(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
56{
57 struct nvkm_device *device = mc->subdev.device;
58 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x000140, 0x00000001);
59}
60
61u32
62nv04_mc_intr_mask(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
63{
64 return nvkm_rd32(mc->subdev.device, 0x000100);
65}
66
67void
68nv04_mc_init(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
69{
70 struct nvkm_device *device = mc->subdev.device;
71 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x000200, 0xffffffff); /* everything enabled */
72 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001850, 0x00000001); /* disable rom access */
73}
74
75static const struct nvkm_mc_func
76nv04_mc = {
77 .init = nv04_mc_init,
78 .intr = nv04_mc_intr,
79 .intr_unarm = nv04_mc_intr_unarm,
80 .intr_rearm = nv04_mc_intr_rearm,
81 .intr_mask = nv04_mc_intr_mask,
82};
83
84int
85nv04_mc_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_mc **pmc)
86{
87 return nvkm_mc_new_(&nv04_mc, device, index, pmc);
88}
